The late King of pop Micheal Jackson's father, Joe Jackson has passed away. According to TMZ, Joe Jackson (89), died yesterday early hours in the morning. Joe had been hospitalised in June for having terminal cancer. He had been experiencing health problems for a while after suffering from a stroke a three heart attacks in 2015. Joe Jackson is by far one of the most successful parent managers, managing the boy group The Jackson Five, the late Micheal Jackson and Janet Jackson's careers. He and his wife Katherine had 11 children together. See tweets below of tributes pouring out:          